==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Figurant
<hw>Fig"u*rant`</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?)</pr>, <pos>n. masc.</pos> <ety>[F.,
prop. p. pr. of <ets>figurer</ets> figure, represent, make a
figure.]</ety> <def>One who dances at the opera, not singly, but in
groups or figures; an accessory character on the stage, who figures in
its scenes, but has nothing to say; hence, one who figures in any scene,
without taking a prominent part.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Figurante</ent>⟦br⟧
